            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Meraioth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 6:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Meraioth is the grandfather of Ahitub, in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 7:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the great-grandfather. But in these genealogies names were freely left out for brevity, and the exact relationship by succession cannot be determined. Names also are repeated in the same family. Meraioth probably occurred often in the line of Seraiah.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the ruler of the house of God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] R.V. omits ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "was",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The same title occurs in connexion curiously enough with the same proper name in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 31:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ‘And Azariah the ruler of the house of God.’ It is tempting to suggest that Azariah’s name has been substituted for that of Seraiah from a gloss on ‘the ruler of the house of God.’ If the title is equivalent to that of the High-priest, then Seraiah is the well-known High-priest, the ancestor of Ezra, put to death by Nebuchadnezzar (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 7:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 25:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). For the use of the title ‘n’gîd’ (Vulg. ‘princeps’), cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 12:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ‘Jehoiada … leader of the house of Aaron.’ But it may denote only a special officer of the Temple. The LXX. renders ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀπέναντι οἴκου τοῦ θεοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (reading ‘",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "neged",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "’ for ‘",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "n’gîd",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "’).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
